  <description type="morphology">Shrubs or trees, 20–70 dm, &lt;usually branched to base&gt;. Leaves: blade ovate or ovate-oblong to narrowly deltate, 4–6 cm, length/width = 1.5, lobes 2–4 per side, lobe apex acute, base broadly cuneate to subtruncate, adaxial surface glabrous, sometimes sparsely appressed-hairy along veins. Inflorescence branches glabrous. Flowers 15–22(–25) mm diam.; stamens 20, anthers pale pink, rarely red.</description>
